					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12863230#post-4450725</guid>
				<title>Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12863230/scp-4943#post-4450725</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 20 Dec 2019 18:09:55 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Attila the Pun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1685633</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While Brain Uploading (as tvtropes calls it) isn't an uncommon trope, most of the stories about it seem to focus on the philosophical questions that come with it. I haven't seen much that covers what it would actually be like for the AI, aside from handwaving it with a physics simulation or the like. What would it look like when you take a copy of someone and then drop it into a computer?</p> <p>This is a story about that.</p> <p>Thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4916887&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="MalyceGraves" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4916887)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/malycegraves" >MalyceGraves</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=392303&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="Voct" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=392303)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/voct" >Voct</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drakimoto" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5255688&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="DrAkimoto" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5255688)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drakimoto" >DrAkimoto</a></span>, and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-fullham" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1989312&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="Doctor Fullham" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1989312)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-fullham" >Doctor Fullham</a></span> for crit!</p> <p>Also, credit goes to these people who <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">were crazy enough to</span> let me use their characters:</p> <ul> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/osiris-wentworth-and-his-wonderful-day-at-work">Osiris Wentworth</a> created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moreworldliness" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5006778&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="MoreWorldliness" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5006778)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/moreworldliness" >MoreWorldliness</a></span></li> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/why-clef-hates-cupcakes">Quinn E. Roscoe</a> created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/detectiveroscoe" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5068157&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="detectiveroscoe" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5068157)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/detectiveroscoe" >detectiveroscoe</a></span></li> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/calibri-bold-s-mega-cool-office">Dr. C. Bold</a> created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/calibri-bold" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5045819&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="Calibri Bold" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5045819)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/calibri-bold" >Calibri Bold</a></span></li> <li><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/michael-sends-his-regards">Dr. Nathaniel Bishop</a> created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themanhattenproject" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3809943&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609620092" alt="TheManhattenProject" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3809943)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/themanhattenproject" >TheManhattenProject</a></span></li> </ul> <p><strong>EDIT 2021/1/2:</strong> I went with the current version of the text logs as a stylistic choice, but I realized later that it might be nice for translators or whoever to know who is talking. So <a href="https://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4943/offset/1">here's a color-coded version!</a></p> 
				 	]]>
